Heat a griddle pan over a high heat or prepare your barbecue until medium hot.Mix the onions, courgettes, aubergine and peppers in a bowl and drizzle with the oil. Season well with salt and pepper and mix well.Meanwhile, put the couscous in a large bowl. Pour in the stock, stir and cover with cling film. Soak for 12–15 minutes.Griddle or barbecue the vegetables in batches for 8–10 minutes, or until just tender.Fluff up the couscous with a fork, then add the herbs, vinegar and grilled vegetables. Stir well, then spoon onto a large platter. Sprinkle with the feta and chilli and serve.